      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Are protein gummies better than protein bars for weight loss?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Protein bars generally deliver more protein per serving (20-30g) but also significantly more calories (200-350 calories), fat (8-15g), and often more sugar (5-15g) than protein gummies. Protein gummies are the better choice when you need a low-calorie protein boost (60-120 calories for 10-15g protein) between meals without adding substantial caloric load. Bars are better when you need a true meal replacement with higher protein density. For weight loss specifically, the lower calorie count of gummies makes them easier to fit into a calorie deficit without compromising satiety benefits.' },
    },
