    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can protein gummies help with weight loss?</summary>
      <p>Protein gummies support weight loss by providing high-protein, low-sugar snacks that promote satiety between meals. A 2015 meta-analysis showed higher protein intake reduces overall caloric intake by suppressing hunger hormones. They work best as between-meal satiety tools within a calorie-controlled diet, not as meal replacements.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How many protein gummies should I eat per day for weight loss?</summary>
      <p>1-2 servings per day as between-meal snacks, timed mid-morning and mid-afternoon when hunger peaks. Factor the 120-240 calories into your daily target. They supplement protein intake during meal gaps, not replace protein-rich meals.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are protein gummies better than protein bars for weight loss?</summary>
      <p>Protein gummies deliver 10-15g protein in 60-120 calories; bars typically deliver 20-30g in 200-350 calories. Gummies are better for low-calorie protein boosts between meals; bars are better for true meal replacement. For calorie deficit management, gummies are easier to fit without caloric surplus.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What type of protein is used in protein gummies?</summary>
      <p>Most use whey protein isolate (best amino acid profile, highest satiety), collagen peptides (good for joints/skin, incomplete amino acids), or plant protein blends (vegan-friendly). For weight loss, whey isolate is preferred for superior satiety signaling.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do protein gummies spike blood sugar?</summary>
      <p>Quality protein gummies with 0-3g sugar do not cause significant spikes. Protein slows gastric emptying, reducing glycemic impact. Check for sugar alcohol type: erythritol (GI of 0) is preferred over maltitol (GI of 36) for blood sugar management.</p>
    </details>

